    Oscar-Claude Monet was a French painter and founder of impressionist painting who is seen as a key precursor to modernism, especially in his attempts to paint nature as he perceived it. Wikipedia

    Died: December 5, 1926, Giverny, France
    Periods: Impressionism, Modern art
    Full name: Oscar-Claude Monet
    Influenced by: douard Manet, Pierre-Auguste Renoir, MORE
